reviews.review_text: A Gem!! This is a high quality audience recording of an incredible, energy filled show that I am very lucky to have happened upon!!WOW-check out Cassidy,Ramble,China-Samson,...the West L.A. is deep down,it's all quality here in my opinion-check it out :-))

4-29-84 One hell of a recording and remaster! I have soundboards of around 2,000 shows at this point. If every aud sounded like this I'd leave most of them sit. Very high energy show. Jerry was making that guitar talk!

high energy grateful dead this show rocks and aud quality very good -- many highlights in both sets and the band careens freight-train style into closing sugar mag. 

jerry on fire all night -- a great thing.

Very Nice Show Well played and seemed inspired to let it rip tonight.
Highlights:  Feels Like A Stranger, Terrapin Station

Terrapin Jam  Of note love the Jam out of Terrapin, and in the 90s this was fairly common but this is a rare occurrence in this era. Might be 1 of the first times they did it until 90? 91? where it became much more common to jam after Terrapin. 
Great show!

CONTRARY TO THE COMPENDIUM REVIEW If any of you are familiar with the TAPER'S COMPENDIUM, make sure to ignore the pathetic review of this show.  The reviewer, who I will not name, wrote this show off as "lifeless, soulless and with NO highlights."  Well, having attended this show in addition to having this fine recording of it, I must say it was a smoker of a show from start to finish.  There are a bunch of highlights, pretty much everything played.  I highly recommend this show!
